<title>HONG KONG: Companion Build year net rises 8.14 pct.</title>
<headline>Companion Build year net rises 8.14 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1996-08-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   19.0	 vs 24.0 (adjusted)</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    2.5	  vs 5.0</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  14.40 gain vs nil</p>
<p>    Net			    91.03	vs 84.18</p>
<p>    Turnover		     939.92     vs 585.53</p>
<p>    Company name		 Companion Building Material</p>
<p>				     (Holdings) Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  September 20-26</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   December 9</p>
<p>NOTE - Companion Building makes ceramic tiles, imports and sells marble and granite products and provides related installation services. It proposed a bonus issue of 1-for-5 shares. Net is after an exceptional gain on disposal of 16.25 percent interest in Companion Marble (BVI) Ltd.</p>
<p>Comparative share earnings have been adjusted for the 1-for-5 bonus issue. The subscription price of the 1997 warrants will be adjusted from HK$1.10 to $0.92 and 1998 warrants from HK$1.25 to $1.04 per share if the bonus issue of shares become unconditional. Total dividend for year is 4.5 cents (including interim dividend of two cents) vs nine cents.</p>
